Background.Name: Heretic
Background.Description: Where gods vie for supremacy through trickery and murder, and mortals ascend to godhood, so there is heresy. You believe in a doctrine outlawed by your faith, taught to you in secret by other heretics. Perhaps your superiors excommunicated you from your temple, or forbidden dogma provided answers to questions you never sought. Whatever your origin, you’re now shunned by the faithful, or worse, hunted.

TableDescription.Name: Heretical Belief
TableDescription.Text: Hundreds of outlawed sects exist throughout the Forgotten Realms. Choose a belief that defines you as a heretic, or roll on the table below.

TableEntry.Title: Dark Moon
TableEntry.Text: A doctrine that ascribes Selúne and Shar as two aspects of the same deity.

TableEntry.Title: Fatemakers
TableEntry.Text: Tymorans who believe mortals can influence and control luck.

TableEntry.Title: Threefold God
TableEntry.Text: A belief that Tyr, Helm and Torm are all the same god.

TableEntry.Title: Forsaken One
TableEntry.Text: A conspiracy that Savras and Leira conceived and abandoned a god child.

TableEntry.Title: Three-Faced Sun
TableEntry.Text: The sun is a tripartite deity, with divine aspects of dawn, noon and dusk.

TableEntry.Title: Shared Suffering
TableEntry.Text: Flagellant Ilmatari who say all mortals must share their god’s suffering.

TableEntry.Title: Entropy
TableEntry.Text: Belief that dying gods sent a divine sphere of annihilation to Toril to kill wizards.

TableEntry.Title: Harlot’s Coin
TableEntry.Text: Belief that Waukeen sold her divinity to Graz’zt and he receives her prayers.

Description.Name: Suggested Characteristics
Description.Text: Heretics survive by living on the run, or by blending into the ranks of greater faiths. They tend to be suspicious folk with zealous ideals and unshakable convictions. This sometimes manifests as a sense of superiority over the “unenlightened”.

ItemChoiceConditionFeature.Name: Equipment
ItemChoiceConditionFeature.Text: A holy symbol (subtly modified to represent your own heretical belief)

ItemChoiceFeature.Name: Equipment
ItemChoiceFeature.Text: A prayer book or prayer wheel

FreeItemAndGoldFeature.Name: Equipment
FreeItemAndGoldFeature.Text: a bottle of invisible ink, a quill, a set of common clothes, and a pouch containing 10 gp.

Feature.Name: Feature: Hereitcal Contacts
Feature.Text: You know where to find heretics in settlements where your faith is represented. If no heretics are present, you can indoctrinate weak-willed souls if you spend a day preaching. Where heretics are present, you can always find a place to hide, rest and recuperate. If needed, they can help you escape the settlement on a cart or through a secret tunnel.

TableEntry.Text: I think I’m right even when I’m wrong.
I pity those who deny the heresy.
I always scope out the closest exits and position myself near them.
Those who refute my beliefs are damned and not worth saving.
I’m sure my god has chosen me for a greater destiny.
I’m a natural orator, but once I start talking it’s difficult for me to stop.
I’m always looking over my shoulder and the slightest things startle me.
I believe the end of the world is nigh.

TableEntry.Title: Guidance
TableEntry.Text: I must teach others my forbidden doctrine (Neutral).

TableEntry.Title: Caution
TableEntry.Text: It’s always better to be safe than sorry (Any).

TableEntry.Title: Knowledge
TableEntry.Text: If this conspiracy is true, what else are we being lied to about? (Neutral)

TableEntry.Title: Insurrection
TableEntry.Text: My old faith is corrupt and must be brought down by the new order (Chaotic).

TableEntry.Title: Honesty
TableEntry.Text: I’ve been lied to enough, so now I’m sworn to always tell the truth (Lawful).

TableEntry.Title: Self-Knowledge
TableEntry.Text: Those who seek the truth become wise beyond their years (Good).
The heretics who educated me were burned at the stake. I won’t let that happen to me.
Belief in my old faith still nags at me. Have I chosen the right path?
I used to be friends with the cleric who’s now hunting me.
I carry a heretical treatise on my person. It mustn’t be found!
I protect the faithless so they can know enlightenment.
One of my underworld contacts reports my movements to the superiors of my old temple.
I’m suspicious of strangers, as they may be bounty hunters sent to arrest me.
I sneer at those whom I deem unworthy of my time.
I’m deeply superstitious, and have many rituals to avoid bad luck.
I tend to misjudge the devotion of others.
I’m obsessed with my studies, often to the detriment of other concerns.
I’m deeply mistrustful of temple hierarchies.
